Anyways so sorry for the long essay lmao I just have a whole lot of thoughts about food, weight, men's view on women's bodies, so on and so forth from growing up always being "overweight" as a woman. But also besides the hypothyroidism, being generally very healthy (with blood pressure, heart rate, general dietary nutrients, physical activity, etc.) so knowing this has been always where my body has tended to naturally be in size, I am very much so not in the mindset anymore of losing weight just to lose weight. I just am also aware of the social implications that very much so do exist and want you to know that and check that you are hopefully not impacted by that.

I am taking the medication to lose weight so that my thyroid medication is more effective so I don't feel as much like shit and exhausted all the time and it will additionally help the effect that the hypothyroidism has on me by making me not feel hungry 24/7 and struggle to feel full even when I am. I generally don't believe in changing my body just for my looks bc I know I just end up being unsuccessful and feeling like shit and I have made so so much progress in liking my body and eating in a way that makes me feel good and is not disordered, so this is truly just a health thing. Though it hopefully would be nice as a side effect for me to be considered closer in attractiveness to how men view you.

but anyways I was also saying that bc of the weight loss medication I am starting and it will hopefully make a difference (though I still very much so am not going to intentionally do anything just for my looks, I am going to eat how I know makes me feel good and how my nutritionist that I used to have recommended and not have strict rules or restrictions bc that's what I have learned is what I need to stay "healthy" - though I don't like that term generally as a black and white descriptor of foods and people - both physically and mentally)

my hope is really that you just find me attractive, I stay secure in my general neutral/somewhat positive view of my own looks, and I hope that you don't get any shit from people about being with me bc that would suck and be unfair to you

btw I just want to let you know I wasn't saying that bc of anything that you did, I have zero issue whatsoever about posting on social media at all, I genuinely do not care (and I haven't posted either bc I don't really share things like that on my account either). I also have no issue at all with pda, I am also not a huge pda person and I appreciate holding hands and whatever but don't need/want much more than that either. this worry has nothing to do at all with anything you've done. it just is from experiences in the past with men calling me ugly, fat, etc. and I know it feels nice to have your friends think your partner is attractive and to be proud of who you're with and so I worry about how people are perceiving me in relation to you in public or if your friends think im ugly/you could do better or whatever. this is just based on me knowing that I am very much so not everyone's type and I don't want you to have to worry about other people judging
